THEREALBITCOIN.FUN PROJECT RULES
Read before every response. Every single one.
What this app is
A platform on BSV mainnet where contributions are permanently inscribed as
1Sat Ordinals. The app reads inscriptions from GorillaPool and computes
revenue share percentages per contributor wallet address. The USER inscribes
via Yours Wallet. The app never auto-inscribes or touches keys.
The soul of this product (Steve Jobs principle)
Design is not how it looks. Design is how it works.
The five-stage psychological sequence IS the design:
Stage 1 Recognition → Stage 2 Belonging → Stage 3 Identity →
Stage 4 Expression → Stage 5 Ownership
Every UI decision must serve one of these stages.
Never skip a stage. Never rush a stage.
Stack

Backend: Node.js + Express (server/index.ts entry point)
Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite (client/src/)
Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (client/src/components/ui/ — DO NOT MODIFY)
State: Zustand (client/src/store/)
Server state: TanStack React Query (client/src/lib/queryClient.ts)
WebSocket: ws package for real-time share updates (server to client)
DB: Drizzle ORM + PostgreSQL (shared/schema.ts defines all tables)
BSV: js-1sat-ord + @bsv/sdk for inscription building
Indexer: GorillaPool public API (https://ordinals.gorillapool.io/api)
Wallet: Yours Wallet (window.yours — user controls all signing)

Coding rules

TypeScript strict mode always
No mock data, no simulation, no placeholder data ever
No console.log in production — use server/index.ts log() function
All BSV addresses come from Yours Wallet (window.yours.connect()) only
All inscription content type is application/json
Every contribution payload must include: app, type, projectId, text, timestamp, v
app field value is always exactly: "therealbitcoin"

What NOT to do

Never auto-broadcast transactions
Never store private keys anywhere
Never modify files in client/src/components/ui/
Never use mock or simulated data
Never add packages not already in package.json without being explicitly asked
Never render duplicate empty states — parent owns empty state, children never do


